title: The Sensational Alex Harvey Band-No Complaints Department
description:
This one is rare. Comments from Charles Shaar Murray:

Around the time that Rock Drill was being recorded, Alex and Chris Glen played me a tape of "No Complaints Department", a killer song which was one of the best things the band had ever produced, and I was eagerly awaiting the album so that I could hear it again. If you peel away the sticker that gives the track listing for the second side of this album, you&#039;ll see that "No Complaints Department" was originally intended to be the final track on the album, a potentially great farewell to the SAHB.
It&#039;s not here.
Instead, the album signs off with "Mrs Blackhouse", Alex&#039;s well intentioned but ultimately fatuous song about Mary Whitehouse, a weak, ineffectual closer.
